ansforming Look of London Underground Subway; Removal Cost Soars|last=Glass|first=Robert|date=12 June 1988|work=Los Angeles Times|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|10 November 1988}}\n|United Kingdom - London\n|Electrocution\n|16\n|A 16-year-old person, who went by the tag \"Rase\", ran away after being seen at Neasden tube depot. He fell onto a live rail, and was electrocuted and killed.\n<ref name=\"Blood on the tracks\"/>\n|-\n|{{dts|29 November 1989}}\n|United States - New York \n|Hit by train\n|17, 17\n|Two 17 year-old people were found dead inside a subway train tunnel, with three spray paint cans. They went by the tags \"Slick\" and \"Soni\".\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.graffiti.org/trains/slickrip.jpg|title=IRT train kills graffiti vandals|last1=Oliver|first1=Chris|last2=Parascandola|first2=Rocco|last3=Nolan|first3=Jim|date=29 November 1989|work=New York Post|access-date=29 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newtimes.co.rw/section/read/184636|title=U5: The making of a social enterprise|last=Opobo|first=Moses|date=4 January 2015|work=The New Times|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref>\n|- \n|{{dts|11 June 1997}}\n|United States - Los Angeles\n|Jumped from height\n|19\n|A 19-year-old person, who went by the tag \"Ozie\", was injured when he jumped 100ft from the top of a concrete pylon, where he had become stranded after spraying graffiti on the side of the Skirball Center overpass above the San Diego Freeway. His injuries included a broken spine, two broken ankles and a broken left arm.\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1997-06-13-me-2972-story.html|title=Graffiti Suspect Hurt in Fall Undergoes Surgery|date=13 June 1997|work=Los Angeles Times|access-date=24 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://apnews.com/bf186c03c5de3cce5d6f6b95ed9bb459|title=Graffiti vandal falls 100 feet from freeway overpass|date=12 June 1997|work=APnews|access-date=24 August 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|1 February 2005}}\n|Canada - Toronto\n|Hit by train\n|18\n|An 18-year-old person, who went by the tag \"Alpha\", was killed when he was hit by a train. He had sprayed his tag on the outside of a freight car. He was then hit by the passing train between Dupont and Christie streets in Toronto.  \n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/a-graffiti-guerrilla-alpha-dies-on-the-job/article4115119/|title=A graffiti guerrilla, Alpha dies on the job|last=Reinhart|first=Anthony|date=3 February 2005|work=The Globe and Mail|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://nowtoronto.com/news/thriving-on-the-thrill/|title=Thriving on the Thrill|first=Conor|last=Clarke|date=17 February 2005|work=NOW Magazine|access-date=17 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.abc.net.au/radionational/programs/archived/streetstories/finding-alpha/3398024|title=Finding Alpha|work=ABC News(Australia)|date=25 March 2007|access-date=17 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|05 January 2007}}\n|United States - New York\n|Hit by Train\n|13\n|A 13-year-old person, who went by the tag \"KOS\", was killed when he was hit by a train. He was with three people who had been writing tags on signal boxes, and got hit by a train.\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/news/death-tracks-graffiti-teen-struck-lirr-train-qns-article-1.261830|title=DEATH ON TRACKS. Graffiti teen struck by LIRR train in Qns|date=5 January 2007|work=nydailynews|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gothamist.com/news/graffitti-tagging-13-year-old-killed-by-lirr-train|title=Graffitti Tagging 13 Year Old Killed by LIRR Train|last=Chung|first=Jen|date=6 January 2007|work=Gothamist|access-date=30 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191229220318/https://gothamist.com/news/graffitti-tagging-13-year-old-killed-by-lirr-train|archive-date=29 December 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://qns.com/story/2007/01/11/teen-killed-on-tracks-buried/|title=Teen killed on tracks buried|last=Christodoulides|first=Alex|date=11 January 2007|work=QNS|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|12 January 2007}}\n|United Kingdom - London\n|Hit by train\n|21, 19\n|Two people were killed after being hit by a train. It occurred between Barking and Upney train stations. They had been spray painting graffiti, attempted to escape after being seen and were hit by a train. They were a 21-year-old person who went by the tag \"Ozone\", and a nineteen-year-old who went by the tag \"Wants\". \n<ref name=\"Blood on the tracks\"/><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/7038509.stm|title=Deadly dangers for graffiti 'taggers'|last=Pankhurst|first=Nigel|date=16 October 2007|work=BBC News|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/england/6267889.stm|title=Tube death was 'pointless waste'|date=16 January 2007|work=BBC News|access-date=1 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|}}\n|France - Paris\n|Electrocution\n|21\n|A 21-year-old person, who went by the tag \"Opea\", was with a fellow tagger Deel in the Paris Metro underground. He bent down to pick up his camera which was on the train track, touched the third rail, was electrocuted by it and killed. \n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.liberation.fr/medias/2007/03/26/les-tagueurs-au-coeur_88497|title=Taggers in the heart|last=Binet|first=Stephanie|date=26 March 2007|work=[[Lib\u00e9ration]]|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailymotion.com/video/x838ll|title=TAG LA GUERRE SOUTERRAINE|last=Hayat|first=Hugo|date=20 January 2009|website=Dailymotion|language=French|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media|url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LRlpaIlx3sY&list=PLFHScc5mjdBDLCzB8LiKnBFsrBD6sOo3R&index=2&t=1331s|title=Graffiti: the forbiden game (full documentary)}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|20 January 2008}}\n|Australia - Sydney\n|Drowned \n|22, 25\n|A 22-year-old person, and a 25-year-old person, died after they were trapped by rising water in a stormwater drain. They were inside a stormwater tunnel painting graffiti when it began raining heavily. The rain swept them to the end of the tunnel which was about one kilometre. Bars at the end of the tunnel prevented them from being able to leave. They then subsequently drowned in the water inside the stormwater drain. \n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2008-01-21/deadly-drain-may-be-closed-off/1018356|title=Deadly drain may be closed off|date=21 January 2008|work=ABC News(Australia)|access-date=7 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theage.com.au/national/farewell-for-storm-drain-graffiti-artist-20080129-ge6nvh.html|title=Farewell for storm drain graffiti artist|last=Dart|first=Jonathan|date=29 January 2008|work=The Age|access-date=7 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/news/nsw/noise-like-a-quake-then-horror/news-story/3e5c3e7ba5297f45acf308ef7cd619d6?sv=513715bd26abade18913fa6826ef0b7e|title=How graffiti pals Holly Legge and Dwane Larosa drowned|website=The Daily Telegraph|date=13 February 2009}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|20 January 2009}}\n|Netherlands - Rotterdam\n|Hit by Train\n|17, 18\n|A metro train was performing a test drive to test points and signals at 4:45am in the morning. It was unusual for trains to travel at this time at night and it was driving in the opposite direction from which trains normally travelled. As it was passing through Slotlaan metro station it struck two people who were a few dozen meters outside the station. It was said at the time the two were likely to have been painting a wall with graffiti. Spray paint cans were found lying next to the railway line. One of the people, 17, was killed from the impact with the train while the second person, 18, was taken to Erasmus medical centre with serious injuries.\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rijnmond.nl/nieuws/21922/Graffitispuiter-17-omgekomen-na-aanrijding-me