a|work=ABC News(Australia)|date=25 March 2007|access-date=17 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|05 January 2007}}\n|United States - New York\n|Hit by Train\n|13\n|A 13-year-old person, who went by the tag \"KOS\", was killed when he was hit by a train. He was with three people who had been writing tags on signal boxes, and got hit by a train.\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/news/death-tracks-graffiti-teen-struck-lirr-train-qns-article-1.261830|title=DEATH ON TRACKS. Graffiti teen struck by LIRR train in Qns|date=5 January 2007|work=nydailynews|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gothamist.com/news/graffitti-tagging-13-year-old-killed-by-lirr-train|title=Graffitti Tagging 13 Year Old Killed by LIRR Train|last=Chung|first=Jen|date=6 January 2007|work=Gothamist|access-date=30 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191229220318/https://gothamist.com/news/graffitti-tagging-13-year-old-killed-by-lirr-train|archive-date=29 December 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://qns.com/story/2007/01/11/teen-killed-on-tracks-buried/|title=Teen killed on tracks buried|last=Christodoulides|first=Alex|date=11 January 2007|work=QNS|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|12 January 2007}}\n|United Kingdom - London\n|Hit by train\n|21, 19\n|Two people were killed after being hit by a train. It occurred between Barking and Upney train stations. They had been spray painting graffiti, attempted to escape after being seen and were hit by a train. They were a 21-year-old person who went by the tag \"Ozone\", and a nineteen-year-old who went by the tag \"Wants\". \n<ref name=\"Blood on the tracks\"/><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/7038509.stm|title=Deadly dangers for graffiti 'taggers'|last=Pankhurst|first=Nigel|date=16 October 2007|work=BBC News|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/england/6267889.stm|title=Tube death was 'pointless waste'|date=16 January 2007|work=BBC News|access-date=1 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|}}\n|France - Paris\n|Electrocution\n|21\n|A 21-year-old person, who went by the tag \"Opea\", was with a fellow tagger Deel in the Paris Metro underground. He bent down to pick up his camera which was on the train track, touched the third rail, was electrocuted by it and killed. \n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.liberation.fr/medias/2007/03/26/les-tagueurs-au-coeur_88497|title=Taggers in the heart|last=Binet|first=Stephanie|date=26 March 2007|work=[[Lib\u00e9ration]]|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailymotion.com/video/x838ll|title=TAG LA GUERRE SOUTERRAINE|last=Hayat|first=Hugo|date=20 January 2009|website=Dailymotion|language=French|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media|url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LRlpaIlx3sY&list=PLFHScc5mjdBDLCzB8LiKnBFsrBD6sOo3R&index=2&t=1331s|title=Graffiti: the forbiden game (full documentary)}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|20 January 2008}}\n|Australia - Sydney\n|Drowned \n|22, 25\n|A 22-year-old person, and a 25-year-old person, died after they were trapped by rising water in a stormwater drain. They were inside a stormwater tunnel painting graffiti when it began raining heavily. The rain swept them to the end of the tunnel which was about one kilometre. Bars at the end of the tunnel prevented them from being able to leave. They then subsequently drowned in the water inside the stormwater drain. \n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2008-01-21/deadly-drain-may-be-closed-off/1018356|title=Deadly drain may be closed off|date=21 January 2008|work=ABC News(Australia)|access-date=7 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theage.com.au/national/farewell-for-storm-drain-graffiti-artist-20080129-ge6nvh.html|title=Farewell for storm drain graffiti artist|last=Dart|first=Jonathan|date=29 January 2008|work=The Age|access-date=7 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/news/nsw/noise-like-a-quake-then-horror/news-story/3e5c3e7ba5297f45acf308ef7cd619d6?sv=513715bd26abade18913fa6826ef0b7e|title=How graffiti pals Holly Legge and Dwane Larosa drowned|website=The Daily Telegraph|date=13 February 2009}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|20 January 2009}}\n|Netherlands - Rotterdam\n|Hit by Train\n|17, 18\n|A metro train was performing a test drive to test points and signals at 4:45am in the morning. It was unusual for trains to travel at this time at night and it was driving in the opposite direction from which trains normally travelled. As it was passing through Slotlaan metro station it struck two people who were a few dozen meters outside the station. It was said at the time the two were likely to have been painting a wall with graffiti. Spray paint cans were found lying next to the railway line. One of the people, 17, was killed from the impact with the train while the second person, 18, was taken to Erasmus medical centre with serious injuries.\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rijnmond.nl/nieuws/21922/Graffitispuiter-17-omgekomen-na-aanrijding-metro#|title=Graffitispuiter (17) omgekomen na aanrijding metro|date=18 October 2009|work=rijnmond|access-date=14 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rijnmond.nl/nieuws/21834/Stille-tocht-voor-Capelse-graffiti-spuiter#|title=Stille tocht voor Capelse graffiti-spuiter|date=21 October 2009|work=rijnmond|access-date=14 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.trouw.nl/nieuws/dode-en-gewonde-door-metro-ongeluk-capelle~b9b50d1e/?referer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.nl%2F|title=Dode en gewonde door metro-ongeluk Capelle|date=18 October 2009|work=Trouw|access-date=14 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|4 July 2010}}\n|United Kingdom - Liverpool\n|Fall\n|22\n|A 22-year-old person, was killed when he fell through a skylight on the roof of a warehouse.The warehouse was between Moorfields and Sandhills railway stations. He was intending to tag the railway line on Sprainger street and had objects with him he could use to tag.  \n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/local-news/tributes-south-road-doorman-steven-6965895|title=Tributes to South Road doorman Steven Longstaffe|date=8 July 2010|work=Liverpool Echo|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/liverpool-news/litherland-doorman-who-died-after-3400768|title=Litherland doorman who died after falling from railway siding was \u2018graffiting\u2019, police believe|date=6 July 2010|work=Liverpool Echo|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-merseyside-11012867|title=Warning after railway trespassing death in Liverpool|date=18 August 2010|work=BBC News|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|9 July 2010}}\n|Germany - Rathenow\n|Hit by train\n|15, 15\n|Two 15 year-old people, were killed by an Ice train after they were spraying graffiti on a freight train carriage. They camped in a tent near the Havel bridge over night in a group of 10. At 7am in the morning the two people left the group and went to the Havel Bridge.  They began to spray a freight train that was located near the Havel bridge. An ICE train approached the pair. The freight train had its engine running and the noise may have been a reason they did not hear the approaching ICE train. The train driver saw them and applied the emergency brakes. The ICE train reached the place on the tracks where they had been spraying. One of the two people was instantly killed from the injuries he suffered from the ICE train. The second of the two was at first taken to hospital and had an arm amputated. He then later died in intensive care. Also present with them at the bridge was a third person aged 12 who witnessed the accident and did not receive any injuries. \n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bz-berlin.de/artikel-archiv/wandgemaelde-fuer-toten-sprayer-gesprueht|title=Sprayed on mural for dead sprayer|date=11 July 2010|work=BZ|access-date=12 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bz-berlin.de/artikel-archiv/der-laute-tod-des-stillen-sprayers|title=The loud death of the silent sprayer|date=9 July 2010|work=BZ|access-date=12 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.maz-online.de/Lokales/Havelland/15-Jaehrige-vom-ICE-erfasst|title=15-year-old captured by the ICE|date=5 November 2014|work=MAZ Online|access-date=12 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.welt.de/vermischtes/weltgeschehen/article8408834/Zweiter-Graffiti-Sprayer-stirbt-nach-ICE-Unglueck.html|title=Second graffiti sprayer dies after ICE accident|date=11 July 2010|work=Welt|access-date=12 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|4 October 2010}}\n|Germany - Berlin\n|Hit by Train\n|31\n|A 31-year-old person, who went by the tag Kmer, was hit by a train and killed. It is thought that Miran was spraying graffiti on a bridge at Karower Kreuz when the collision with the train occurred. The driver of the train was unaware that any collision had occurred. His body was thrown from the bridge by the train into bushes near by. One news source reported that it had been guessed as 3 or 4 days the length of time that the body had been in the bushes, although it remained uncertain. \n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bz-berlin.de/artikel-archiv/graffiti-sprayer-tot-im-gleisbett-gefunden|title=Graffiti sprayer found dead in the track bed|date=12 October 2008|work=BZ|access-date=1 January 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"In the name of the can\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.tagesspiegel.de/berlin/stadtleben/graffiti-sprueher-in-berlin-im-namen-der-dose/1396594.html|title=In the name of the can|date=15 December 2012|work=Tagesspiegel|access-date=1 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts| 23 October 2010}}\n|Poland - Prabuty\n|Hit by Train\n|19\n|A 19-year-old person was on the railway tracks in Prabuty. They were there with some people who were spray painting graffiti. The 19 year-old had finished spray painting the wall of a viaduct. It is thought that he then went to paint a freight train that was slowly travelling past. An oncoming train sounded its siren. It is thought possible that they leaned out from behind a freight wagon. It has been reported that ''\"The rush of air pulled the teenager right under the wheels of the train\"''.<ref name=\"Fakt24 Shock! He killed himself by graffiti!2010\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.fakt.pl/wydarzenia/polska/szok-zabil-sie-przez-graffiti/xy1e94c#slajd-1|title=Shock! He killed himself by graffiti!|last=TON|date=27 October 2020|work=Fakt24pl|access-date=17 January 2019}}</ref> The person was killed instantly from the collision.\n<ref name=\"Fakt24 Shock! He killed himself by graffiti!2010\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.portalpomorza.pl/wiadomosci/30601,maszynista-pociagu-ostrzegal-syrena-karol-nie-zdazyl-uciec-przed-pociagiem|title=The train driver warned with a siren. Karol did not manage to escape from the train|date=11 November 2010|work=portalpomorza|access-date=17 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://kwidzyn.naszemiasto.pl/prabuty-grafficiarz-zginal-na-torach/ar/c16-628964|title=\nPrabuty. Grafficiarz was killed on the tracks|date=25 October 2010|work=kwidzynnaszemiasto|access-date=17 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|31 October 2010}}\n|Canada - Montreal\n|Hit by train\n|17, 17, 17\n|Three 17 year-old people were killed after being hit by a train. They were intending to spray paint graffiti under the Turcot interchange.  Two cars belonging to the graffiti artists were found nearby and a red spray can was found in one of the cars. It is thought that the Viarail train was quiet as it travelled down the tracks and they did not hear it coming. After the accident it was recommendation was handed down to Transport Canada to review the practice of putting a trains headlights  into standby. Two other people who were with them at the time were uninjured. Two of the people went by the tags \"Jays\" and \"Aber\". \n<ref>{{Cite