135\n|head_coach=[[Amy Vachon]] (Interim)<br>[[Richard Barron (basketball)|Richard Barron]]\n|hc_year = 7th\n|asst_coach1=Jhasmin Player\n|asst_coach2=Courtney Anderson England\n|asst_coach3=Garett Sherman\n|asst_coach4=\n|stadium=[[Memorial Gymnasium (University of Maine)|Memorial Gym]]<br>[[Cross Insurance Center]]\n|champion=America East Regular Season and Tournament champions\n|bowl=NCAA Women's Tournament\n|bowl_result=First Round\n}}\n{{2017\u201318 America East Conference women's basketball standings}}\nThe '''2017\u201318 Maine Black Bears women's basketball''' team represented the [[University of Maine]] [[Maine Black Bears|Black Bears]] in the [[2017\u201318 NCAA Division I women's basketball season]]. The Black Bears, led by seventh year head coach [[Richard Barron (basketball)|Richard Barron]] and interim head coach Amy Vachon, play their home games at the [[Cross Insurance Center]] with 2 games played at [[Memorial Gymnasium (University of Maine)|Memorial Gym]] and are members of the [[America East Conference]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goblackbears.com/documents/2016/11/4/2016_17_WBB_Media_Guide.pdf |title=University of Maine Athletics |publisher=Goblackbears.com |date= |accessdate=2017-11-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/womens-college-basketball/team/_/id/311/maine-black-bears |title=Maine Black Bears Women's Basketball - Black Bears News, Scores, Stats, Rumors & More |publisher=ESPN |date= |accessdate=2017-11-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Maine Black Bears |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/ncaaw/teams/maa/ |title=Maine Black Bears on Yahoo! Sports - News, Scores, Standings, Rumors, Fantasy Games |publisher=Sports.yahoo.com |date= |accessdate=2017-11-02}}</ref> They finished the season 23\u201310, 15\u20131 in America East play to win the America East Regular Season. They also won of the [[2018 America East Women's Basketball Tournament|America East Women's Tournament]] and earn an automatic trip to the [[2018 NCAA Division I Women's Basketball Tournament|NCAA Women's Tournament]] for the first time since 2004. They lost to Texas in the first round.\n\n==Media==\nAll home games and conference road games will stream on either [[ESPN3]] or AmericaEast.tv. Most road games will stream on the opponents website. All games will be broadcast on the radio on [[WGUY]] and online on the [http://client.stretchinternet.com/client/maine.portal Maine Portal].\n\n==Roster==\n{{CBB roster/Header|sex=w|year=2017|team=Maine Black Bears| teamcolors=y|high_school=y}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Sierra|last=Tapley|link=n|num=2|pos=G|ft=5|in=8|class=SO|rs=|home=[[Bar Harbor, Maine|Bar Harbor, ME]]|high_school=[[Mount Desert Island High School|Mount Desert Island]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Maddy|last=McVicar|link=n|num=4|pos=G|ft=5|in=4|class=JR|rs=|home=[[Calais, Maine|Calais, ME]]|high_school=[[Calais High School|Calais]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Maeve|last=Carroll|link=n|num=5|pos=F|ft=5|in=11|class=FR|rs=|home=[[Oakton, Virginia|Oakton, VA]]|high_school=[[Georgetown Visitation Preparatory School|Georgetown Visitation Preparatory]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Julie|last=Brosseau|link=y|num=10|pos=G|ft=5|in=8|class=SO|rs=|home=[[Repentigny, Quebec|Repentigny, QE]]|high_school=[[Coll\u00e8ge Montmorency]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Parise|last=Rossignol|link=n|num=12|pos=G|ft=5|in=8|class=JR|rs=|home=[[Van Buren, Maine|Van Buren, ME]]|high_school=[[Van Buren High School (Van Buren, Maine)|Van Buren]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Dor|last=Saar|link=n|num=15|pos=G|ft=5|in=6|class=FR|rs=|home=[[Ma'anit|Ma'anit, Israel]]|high_school=[[Israeli Basketball Academy]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Kelly|last=Fogarty|link=n|num=20|pos=G|ft=5|in=9|class=FR|rs=|home=[[Walpole, Massachusetts|Walpole, MA]]|high_school=[[Walpole High School|Walpole]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Blanca|last=Millan|link=n|num=22|pos=G|ft=5|in=11|class=SO|rs=|home=[[Santiago de Compostela|Santiago de Compostela, Spain]]|high_school=[[Colegio Manuel Peleteiro]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Tanesha|last=Sutton|link=n|num=23|pos=G|ft=5|in=10|class=JR|rs=y|home=[[Philadelphia|Philadelphia, PA]]|high_school=[[Saints John Neumann and Maria Goretti Catholic High School|Ss. Neumann and Goretti]]<br>[[Duquesne Dukes women's basketball|Duquesne]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Kat|last=Williams|link=n|num=31|pos=C|ft=6|in=5|class=FR|rs=|home=[[Coral Springs, Florida|Coral Springs, FL]]|high_school=[[Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School|Marjory Stoneman Douglas]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Kira|last=Barra|link=n|num=32|pos=F|ft=6|in=3|class=FR|rs=|home=[[Dillingen an der Donau|Dillingen, Germany]]|high_school=[[Theo Koch Schule]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Kirsten|last=Johnson|link=n|num=33|pos=F|ft=6|in=2|class=SR|rs=|home=[[San Diego|San Diego, CA]]|high_school=[[The Academy of Our Lady of Peace|Academy of Our Lady Peace]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Fanny|last=Wadling|link=n|num=51|pos=F|ft=6|in=1|class=SO|rs=|home=[[Nacka|Nacka, Sweden]]|high_school=[[Lule\u00e5 Praktiska Gymnasium]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Footer\n|head_coach=\n* [[Amy Vachon]] ({{college|Maine}})\n|asst_coach=\n* Jhasmin Player ({{college|Baylor}})\n* Courtney Anderson England ({{college|Maine}})\n* Garett Sherman ({{college|Frostburg State}})\n|roster_url=http://goblackbears.com/roster.aspx?path=wbball\n|accessdate=\n}}\n\n==Schedule==\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goblackbears.com/schedule.aspx?path=wbball |title=University of Maine Athletics |publisher=Goblackbears.com |date= |accessdate=2017-11-02}}</ref>\n{{CBB schedule start|time=|rank=|ranklink=[[2017\u201318 NCAA Division I women's basketball rankings]]|rankyear=2017|tv=|record=yes|attend=yes}}\n|-\n!colspan=9 style=\"background:#{{NCAA color|Maine Black Bears|1}}; color:white;\"| Exhibition\n{{CBB schedule entry\n| date         = 10/28/2017\n| time         = 5:00 PM \n| w/l          = l\n| nonconf      = yes\n| 